&lt;p&gt;The provided document is an &lt;strong&gt;Implementation Matrix (Table 6.1.1)&lt;/strong&gt; from a &lt;strong&gt;Strategic Plan (2023-2027)&lt;/strong&gt; by &lt;strong&gt;The National Treasury and Economic Planning&lt;/strong&gt;. It outlines the strategies, key activities, expected outputs, targets, budget allocation, and responsibility for various initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The matrix covers six main strategic areas:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;1. Budget Process and PFM Staff Capacity Building (Strategy 3.9)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus:&lt;/strong&gt; Enhancing transparency, digitization, and staff capacity in the budget process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Activities:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting public participation on the National Budget (5 forums targeted over 5 years).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digitization and Automation (100% target):&lt;/strong&gt; Developing a Budget Portal and automating In-Year Budget Changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Capacity Building:&lt;/strong&gt; Training PFM Staff on the Budget Process (Targets: 839 County PFM Staff and 2,004 National Government PFM Officers).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibility:&lt;/strong&gt; Primarily the &lt;strong&gt;Budget Department&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;ALL TNT Directorates&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Budget (5-Year Total):&lt;/strong&gt; Approximately Ksh. 325 million for public participation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;2. Efficiency in Pensions Administration and Management (Strategic Objective 3.10)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus:&lt;/strong&gt; Streamlining pension application and disbursement, strengthening policy, and building a digital infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Activities:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Optimization (100% target):&lt;/strong&gt; Implementing workflow analysis and technology upgrades.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Claims Monitoring:&lt;/strong&gt; Developing a system to identify and fast-track aged claims.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Training (300 staff target):&lt;/strong&gt; Developing and conducting training sessions for departmental staff on benefit processing, focusing on error prevention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Policy and Legal Framework:&lt;/strong&gt; Reviewing and developing new policy and legislative proposals (5 new policies/amendments targeted).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digital Database (1 targeted):&lt;/strong&gt; Establishing a digital database for the identification and registration of pensioners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expert Advice (100% target):&lt;/strong&gt; Providing prompt expert advice on public service pensions to various agencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibility:&lt;/strong&gt; Primarily the &lt;strong&gt;Pension Department&lt;/strong&gt; with support from &lt;strong&gt;SCMS, HRM&amp;amp;D, Finance Unit, CPPMD,&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Legal Unit&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;3. Strengthening Public Investment Management Framework (Strategic Objective 3.11)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus:&lt;/strong&gt; Developing standards for the preparation and appraisal of public investment projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Activities:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing &lt;strong&gt;15 Standard Manuals&lt;/strong&gt; (Guidelines) for sector-specific standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and maintaining a &lt;strong&gt;Bank of Projects&lt;/strong&gt; within the Public Investment Management Information System (PIMIS) (100% completion targeted).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibility:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;PIM&lt;/strong&gt; (Lead) and &lt;strong&gt;PIMIS&lt;/strong&gt; (Support).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;4. Development Finance and Portfolio Review (Strategy 1.2)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus:&lt;/strong&gt; Establishing financing frameworks, resource mobilization, and monitoring development projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Activities:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and operationalizing a &lt;strong&gt;Green Financing Framework&lt;/strong&gt; (1 targeted).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing a &lt;strong&gt;Resource Mobilization Strategy&lt;/strong&gt; (1 targeted).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertaking periodical portfolio review and assessment (20 review meetings and 20 reports targeted).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building capacity for M&amp;amp;E on the management of development programmes (5 reports targeted).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibility:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;PDAD&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;RMD&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;5. Enhancing Public Debt Management Efficiency and Transparency (Strategic Objective 1.3)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus:&lt;/strong&gt; Strengthening debt management regulations, policy, and system integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Activities:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing &lt;strong&gt;Regulations/Guidelines&lt;/strong&gt; (1 targeted) and a &lt;strong&gt;Contingent Liability Management Policy&lt;/strong&gt; (1 targeted).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing &lt;strong&gt;15 Reports&lt;/strong&gt; on Medium Term Debt Management Strategies and Annual Public Debt and Guarantee Performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Integration (100% target for all):&lt;/strong&gt; Integrating the Meridian Debt Management System with PFMIS, and integrating the Meridian CSD system with GOK GROW/Central Securities Depository.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibility:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;PDAD&lt;/strong&gt; (Lead), &lt;strong&gt;DPSSM,&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;DHS&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;6. Increasing Private Capital Investments in PPPs (Strategic Objective 1.4)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus:&lt;/strong&gt; Supporting the development of Public-Private Partnership (PPP) projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Activities:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting Authorities in the preparation of PPP projects and transactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target:&lt;/strong&gt; Supporting &lt;strong&gt;48&lt;/strong&gt; Feasibility Studies/High-Risk projects over five years.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibility:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;PPP&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Budget (5-Year Total):&lt;/strong&gt; Ksh. 10,200 million (the largest allocation in the provided tables).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

